{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1446297175,"nonce":"RtiAxr4t/47IgezAyp7SslrIVxY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE1MjczNDY5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/364#issuecomment-152734693"},"message":"@nsoranzo in general I like the idea of merging wrappers and converging to one high quality wrapper.\nTwo points to consider/discuss:\n1) Do we want to minimize the functional overlap of our tools? In other words, again a new trimmer? Do we need it?\n2) Currently, `non-iuc` repositories can have some disadvantages. \n- No one knows which one of the above three is the preferred IUC one (star'ring of repositories does not work yet).\n- Write permission can be revoked or any other harm can happen which we can not control (repository redirections are missing)\n\nMaybe, I'm just too pessimistic but we should be aware of this and under some circumstances it might be better to create a IUC repository for such tools. That said, as soon as we have proper star'ing and redirection of repositories these problems are obsolete.\n\nOpinions?","files":null}]}